Social Engineering Toolkit
Framework for social engineering attacks

Social Engineering
Description
The Social-Engineer Toolkit (SET) is a penetration testing framework designed for social engineering. It has many attack vectors to exploit human weaknesses.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which setoolkit
Install command:

sudo apt install set
Basic Syntax
sudo setoolkit
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
sudo setoolkit

Launch SET	Start social engineering	
Option 1: Social-Engineering Attacks

Main attack menu	Choose attack type	
Option 2: Website Attack Vectors

Web-based attacks	Credential harvesting	
Option 3: Credential Harvester

Clone sites for creds	Phishing setup	
